			<ns0:name>robertm@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/robertm@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">the existing arm trusted TC has a number of problems which should be cleaned up.
This will make it easier to migrate to a different TC.
The problems are:
* use of an awkward setup script  tools/llvm/setup_arm_trusted_toolchain.py
  (this used to be a shell script and was used for other components as well
   but now scons seems to be the only client so we may as well inline it
* we use armv6 which is probably not quite accurate (some .S files apparently 
   already use armv7 instructions
* we force everything "-static" while still building some shared libs
* ...




